# ── aDNA workspace .gitignore ─────────────────────────────────────────
# The tracked base = CLAUDE.md, README.md, LICENSE, .adna/, this file.
# Everything a USER creates in the workspace is ignored by design:
# projects are self-contained sibling repos, never committed here.

# User projects — each <Name>.aDNA/ directory is its own git repo.
# Pattern note: `?*` requires a non-empty name so this can NEVER match
# the embedded `.adna/` base (which is case-insensitively `.aDNA` on
# macOS/Windows filesystems); the explicit negation is belt-and-braces.
/?*.aDNA/
!/.adna/

# Workspace working dirs (created as you use the system) — root-anchored
# so they never shadow paths inside .adna/.
/modules/
/lattices/
/datasets/
/results/
/shared/
/_archive/

# Agent harness + environment
/.claude/
.env
.env.*
.mcp.json

# Workspace-level Obsidian per-device state (if you open ~/aDNA/ itself as a vault)
/.obsidian/

# OS junk
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Python
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.venv/
venv/

# Milestone tarballs at workspace root
/*.tar.gz
